    • add

      public void add​(java.lang.Object o)
      The element is inserted immediately before the next element that would be returned by next, if any, and after the next element that would be returned by previous if any. (If the list contains no elements, the new element becomes the sole element on the list.) The new element is inserted before the implicit cursor: a subsequent call to next would be unaffected, and a subsequent call to previous would return the new element.
      Specified by:
      add in interface HListIterator
      Parameters:
      o - the element to insert.
